Coffeyville Resources Flares Gases at Plant After Power Outage

-- B y   M a r i o   P a r k e r   a n d   A a r o n   C l a r k
-- 
2011-04-24T18:34:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-24/coffeyville-resources-flares-gases-at-plant-after-power-outage.html
Coffeyville Resources LLC, a
refining and chemical company owned by  CVR Energy Inc. (CVI) , released
sulfur dioxide and hydrogen sulfide after a  power outage  at its
plant in Coffeyville,  Kansas , on April 21, state authorities
said.  The state said that it didn’t have any additional details
because the incident reports haven’t been filed yet.  To contact the reporter responsible for this story:
Mario Parker in Chicago at 
 mparker22@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Stets at 
 dstets@bloomberg.net . 